**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- User-controlled type selection allows instantiation of unintended types
- No input size limits enable denial-of-service via memory exhaustion
- Deserializing into `interface{}` accepts any structure without validation
- Error messages leak internal implementation details
- No validation of deserialized data before processing

**SECURE VERSION**:

